{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"09b49e58-a3a1-44fa-80c5-cb56e190eb99","content":"Here's what I've created and what you need to do:\n\n## Workflow: `.github/workflows/publish.yml`\n\nTriggers on version tags (`v*`), packs your library, and pushes to NuGet — **no API key needed** because `id-token: write` enables OIDC.\n\n## You must configure NuGet.org\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org/account/settings/trusted-publishers), add a **Trusted Publisher** with:\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Repository owner | `myorg` |\n| Repository name | `mylib` |\n| Workflow filename | `publish.yml` |\n| Environment | *(leave blank)* |\n\n## To publish\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe workflow will authenticate via OIDC automatically — no `NUGET_API_KEY` secret required. Make sure your `.csproj` has `<PackageId>`, `<Version>`, and other required package metadata.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e3840f88-1d7e-4b62-ae39-d52c774baeea","outputTokens":250,"requestId":"1402:4B044:1B57183:1E702FE:69FA90E0"},"id":"501822d9-5a73-4cf7-9fd1-d334e48412b9","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:52:55.350Z","parentId":"ede7f58b-890b-4d85-8deb-f2328fb214c0"}
